    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.19.3-4_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">3</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Oglala <hi rend="caps">S D</hi>
                        Dec 16, 1940
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <note type="curatorial">[Neihardt Branson Mo]</note>
                
                    <salute>Dear Son:-</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Well you'll be surprised to hear from you because I don't know why you never write to me but I still remember you folks so here I am writing to you and your family</p>
                
                <p>First of all I will say we're all getting along fine even up to Ben + his family Well the weather is <unclear>partly</unclear> cold up here but quite a few snow</p>
                
                <p>For 5 yrs successive I've been in the Bl Hills for the summer + pretty busy putting up a show for <unclear/> so I really forgot to write to my friends</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.19.3-4_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">4</fw>
                <fw type="authorial">II</fw>
                
                <p>Well theres any news except that we're hearing about the War all the time</p>
                
                <p>I hope you enjoy your holidays and may the Great Spirit bring lots of blessings</p> 
                
                <p>I'm yours truly father</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Nick Black Elk Sr.</signed>
                    <address><addrLine>Oglala <hi rend="caps">S.D.</hi></addrLine></address>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
